Spring Boot and OAuth2
This part of Spring  starts with a simple, single-provider single-sign on, and works up to a client with a 
choice of authentication providers.
The simples are all single-page apps using Spring Boot and Spring Security on the back end. 
Securing the Application with GitHub and Spring Security
To make the application secure, you can simply add Spring Security as a dependency. 
